      "text": {
        "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Problem\">Problem</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_BMO_Problems/Problem_2&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Problem\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>(<i>Bogdan Enescu, Romania</i>)\nIf <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/1/7/317096889b84df0b72bf69ceb4c82208305f1b0f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$n \\ge 2$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"43\" height=\"14\" /> is an integer and <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/5/6/4564100398ca63b543439077b5180abb7f9840d2.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$0 &lt; a_1 &lt; a_2 \\dotsb &lt; a_{2n+1}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"180\" height=\"16\" /> are real numbers, prove the inequality:\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/0/6/106bb9c8b449da5e9ce35a76e883c57b6ab141e6.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\sqrt[n]{a_1} - \\sqrt[n]{a_2} + \\sqrt[n]{a_3} -\\dotsb - \\sqrt[n]{a_{2n}} + \\sqrt[n]{a_{2n+1}} &lt; \\sqrt[n]{a_1 -a_2 +a_3 - \\dotsb -a_{2n} + a_{2n+1}} .\\]\" width=\"590\" height=\"19\" />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Solution\">Solution</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_BMO_Problems/Problem_2&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Solution\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Let us denote <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/3/8/93840ec24824444aa3de4a28cf7819cdf7440d7d.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$d= a_1 - a_2 + a_3 - \\dotsb - a_{2n} + a_{2n+1}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"282\" height=\"16\" />, and let us denote <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/b/1/eb1509af693bd5b71dec6e9d1797e0e7afd1b181.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$S= \\sum_{i=0}^n a_{2i+1}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -20px\" width=\"101\" height=\"48\" />.  We note at first that\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/6/d/16d124b03e3d06ca8eea23b2d8db51928c17f465.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[d = a_1 + (a_3-a_2) + \\dotsb + (a_{2n+1} - a_{2n}) &gt; a_1 + 0 + \\dotsb + 0 &gt; 0.\\]\" width=\"478\" height=\"18\" />\n</p><p><b>Lemma.</b> <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/7/5/a75540fefa2a89e7cd3e5297e82f100e15e3458c.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$(a_1, a_3, \\dotsc, a_{2n+1}) \\succ (a_2, a_4, \\dotsc, a_2, d)$\" style=\"vertical-align: -5px\" width=\"296\" height=\"20\" />\n</p><p><i>Proof.</i>  Evidently, the two sequences have sum <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/d/2/ad28c83c99a8fd0dd2e2e594c9d02ee532765a0a.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$S$\" style=\"vertical-align: -1px\" width=\"14\" height=\"14\" />.  Let <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/c/3/8c325612684d41304b9751c175df7bcc0f61f64f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$k$\" width=\"9\" height=\"12\" /> be the least integer such that <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/2/8/828d3ce78ff22fae48f4e858eb1bcbd30332c2f3.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$a_{2k} \\ge d$\" style=\"vertical-align: -2px\" width=\"58\" height=\"15\" />.  We now note that for integers <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/0/0/e/00ef22e26a4e5ca81c8912759ee9543c9ca59147.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$k\\le j \\ge n$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"77\" height=\"16\" />,\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/9/2/a/92a9e3027499fae7e9545acc2254fa8bd2054281.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\sum_{i=j}^n a_{2i+1} &gt; \\sum_{i=j}^n a_{2i},\\]\" width=\"145\" height=\"49\" />\nand for integers <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/1/b/b/1bb9a2dd8b51bb5137afd1f6b73ca043329cb334.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$0\\le j &lt;k$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"75\" height=\"16\" />,\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/4/c/a4cca0b21fc291ba14cf1e40d16bd928a11ea37c.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\sum_{i=j}^n a_{2i+1} = S - \\sum_{i=1}^{j} a_{2i-1} \\ge S - \\sum_{i=1}^j a_{2i},\\]\" width=\"306\" height=\"54\" />\nwhich is the sum of the <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/e/d/e/edee97ef08bc70e95315552628fa61dda666c871.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$n-j$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"40\" height=\"16\" /> smallest terms of the second sequence.  Equality holds when <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/8/4/9/8491cdd7734fa4e048d0883176399057c4badc6f.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$j=0$\" style=\"vertical-align: -4px\" width=\"44\" height=\"17\" />.  Therefore the first sequence <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/Majorize\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Majorize\">majorizes</a> the second, as was to be proven.  <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/b/b/3bbb9e25e5be095e317771a9c5d00877ee9c8012.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\blacksquare$\" width=\"13\" height=\"12\" />\n</p><p>Now, since the function <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/7/d/7/7d7935b44d63554df8f8eb18ddf17a2311c4ce9c.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$f: x \\mapsto \\sqrt[n]{x}$\" style=\"vertical-align: -3px\" width=\"92\" height=\"18\" /> is strictly <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/Concave\" title=\"Concave\">concave</a> and our two sequences are not equal, by <a href=\"/wiki/index.php/Karmata%27s_Inequality\" title=\"Karmata&#39;s Inequality\">Karmata's Inequality</a>\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/4/7/4/47445b1bf5fb6455cb4619edc069ee1949d9d1c2.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\sqrt[n]{a_1} + \\sqrt[n]{a_3} + \\dotsb + \\sqrt[n]{a_{2n+1}} &lt; \\sqrt[n]{a_2} + \\dotsb + \\sqrt[n]{a_{2n}} + \\sqrt[n]{d},\\]\" width=\"433\" height=\"23\" />\nor\n<img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/a/7/9/a798bd417ebd52e0e84669501ff6c244585fa697.png\" class=\"latexcenter\" alt=\"\\[\\sqrt[n]{a_1} - \\sqrt[n]{a_2} + \\sqrt[n]{a_3} - \\dotsb - \\sqrt[n]{a_{2n}} + \\sqrt[n]{a_{2n+1}} &lt; \\sqrt[n]{d},\\]\" width=\"390\" height=\"23\" />\nas desired.  <img src=\"//latex.artofproblemsolving.com/3/b/b/3bbb9e25e5be095e317771a9c5d00877ee9c8012.png\" class=\"latex\" alt=\"$\\blacksquare$\" width=\"13\" height=\"12\" />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Resources\">Resources</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_BMO_Problems/Problem_2&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Resources\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/index.php?title=1998_BMO_Problems&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"1998 BMO Problems (page does not exist)\">1998 BMO Problems</a></li>\n<li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.artofproblemsolving.com/viewtopic.php?p=495395#p495395\">Discussion on AoPS/MathLinks</a></li></ul>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20240907211002\nCache expiry: 86400\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.026 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.028 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 199/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 436/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 0/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 0/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 2/40\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 4243/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%    0.000      1 -total\n-->\n</div>\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki-wiki_:pcache:idhash:6099-0!canonical and timestamp 20240907211002 and revision id 21692\n -->\n"
